</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="27" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="27">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="27">
No specimens are cited by de 
<bibRefCitation author="Vriese, WH de" journalOrPublisher="Systematic Biology" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" refId="B75" refString="Vriese, WH de, 1854. Goodenovieae. Natuurkundige Verhandelingen van de Hollandsche Maatschappij der Wetenschappen te Haarlem ser. 2, 10." title="Goodenovieae. Natuurkundige Verhandelingen van de Hollandsche Maatschappij der Wetenschappen te Haarlem ser. 2, 10." year="1854">Vriese (1854)</bibRefCitation>
in the protologue for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="de Vriese" authorityYear="1854" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Goodeniaceae" genus="Dampiera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Dampiera verreauxii" order="Asterales" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="verreauxii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">Dampiera verreauxii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, although de Vriese indicates that he examined material of this taxon made available by Verreaux at the 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Muséum">Museum</normalizedToken>
National 
<normalizedToken originalValue="d’Histoire">d'Histoire</normalizedToken>
Naturelle in Paris (P) in 1850. Verreaux visited Australia during 1842-1846 but his collecting efforts were confined to Tasmania and the east coast of Australia (
<bibRefCitation author="George, AS" journalOrPublisher="Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" refId="B37" refString="George, AS, 2009. Australian botanist's companion. Four Gables Press, Kardinya, Western Australia." title="Australian botanist's companion. Four Gables Press, Kardinya, Western Australia." year="2009">George 2009</bibRefCitation>
) and so it is unlikely he would have obtained material from Western Australia directly. 
<bibRefCitation author="Carolin, RC" editor="George, AS" journalOrPublisher="35. Australian Government Publishing Service, Canberra" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" pagination="298 - 300" refId="B25" refString="Carolin, RC, 1992i. Verreauxia. In: George, AS, Ed., Flora of Australia vol. 35. Australian Government Publishing Service, Canberra: 298 - 300" title="Verreauxia." volumeTitle="Flora of Australia vol." year="1992 i">Carolin (1992i)</bibRefCitation>
postulated that &quot;The type was probably collected by J. Drummond (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">Drummond</emphasis>
4: 186 cited by Krause, loc. cit. [= Pflanzenr. 54: 170 (1912)])&quot;. This is possible, as Drummond did collect extensively through south-west Western Australia (including the region where this species occurs) and his specimens were sent to various institutions throughout Australia and Europe. Three Drummond collections of this taxon have been located (MEL 42188 [image!], P 03035588 [image!] and P 04057856 [image!]). However, it is not clear whether these specimens represent original material and neither specimen at P is an exact match for the plant illustrated in the protologue. Accordingly, the illustration included in the protologue is here designated as the lectotype for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="de Vriese" authorityYear="1854" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Goodeniaceae" genus="Dampiera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Dampiera verreauxii" order="Asterales" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="verreauxii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">Dampiera verreauxii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
de Vriese.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
